WEBVTT

00:01.069 --> 00:02.603
Previously on
"The Good Doctor"...

00:02.636 --> 00:05.239
Is there something
you're not telling me?
When we're in
meetings together,

00:06.074 --> 00:07.508
don't ever call my ideas
"ridiculous."

00:07.541 --> 00:08.542
Come on.
I'm being serious.

00:08.576 --> 00:09.710
So am I.

00:09.743 --> 00:11.512
Merrill's son asked
for personal advice.

00:11.545 --> 00:13.447
And he picked you.
I know, right?

00:13.481 --> 00:16.317
A surgeon needs to communicate.
Can Dr. Murphy do that?

00:16.350 --> 00:17.485
Can he do that under stress?

00:17.518 --> 00:19.720
Can he do that knowing
that a human life

00:19.753 --> 00:21.655
literally hangs in the balance?

00:26.360 --> 00:28.462
Farrar:
Thank you, Dr. Kalu.

00:28.496 --> 00:30.231
Jared: You're welcome.
It's a special blend.

00:30.264 --> 00:32.466
I roast the beans myself.

00:32.500 --> 00:34.268
Smells like leather.

00:34.302 --> 00:36.237
Then none for you,
Murphy.

00:36.270 --> 00:39.240
I don't drink coffee.

00:39.273 --> 00:40.241
[ Mugs clink ]

00:40.274 --> 00:41.609
It is dead in here.

00:41.642 --> 00:43.544
That's why they call it
the graveyard shift.

00:43.577 --> 00:46.747
Oh, well, I call it paradise.
You my trauma virgins?

00:46.780 --> 00:49.583
Ah, Doctors Murphy,
Kalu, Browne --

00:49.617 --> 00:51.085
meet Dr. Audrey Lim,

00:51.119 --> 00:52.420
your attending
for the evening.

00:52.453 --> 00:53.487
Hey.
Coffee?

00:53.521 --> 00:55.089
He roasts the beans
himself.

00:55.123 --> 00:57.491
Oh. Kiss ass.

00:57.525 --> 00:59.493
[ Laughs ]

00:59.527 --> 01:00.794
E.R.

01:02.763 --> 01:05.299
How long?
Got it.

01:05.333 --> 01:06.400
Listen up, everybody!

01:06.434 --> 01:07.801
We got a mass cas
coming in.

01:07.835 --> 01:09.737
It's a bus crash,
two dozen passengers.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.605
Transfer all patients
waiting for beds

01:11.639 --> 01:13.107
up to the nursing units.

01:13.141 --> 01:14.642
Have maintenance
bring down cots.

01:14.675 --> 01:16.710
We're gonna convert
the waiting room into triage.

01:16.744 --> 01:18.579
No one goes home
till we're all clear!

01:18.612 --> 01:20.514
Dr. Lim:
Page everyone on call. I don't
care what department they are.

01:20.548 --> 01:23.851
Tonight, everybody's trauma.
Glove up and line up.

01:23.884 --> 01:32.160
**

01:32.193 --> 01:33.727
EMTs will have triaged onsite,

01:33.761 --> 01:35.563
so the patients
are gonna come in tagged.

01:37.165 --> 01:39.267
I love these blank faces
right before Armageddon.

01:39.300 --> 01:40.301
Trauma color coding --
who knows it?

01:40.334 --> 01:42.603
Green -- walking wounded.
Yellow -- observation.

01:42.636 --> 01:44.138
Red needs immediate
attention.

01:44.172 --> 01:45.806
And black go straight
to the morgue.

01:45.839 --> 01:52.680
**

01:52.713 --> 01:55.316
[ Sirens wail ]

01:55.349 --> 01:59.553
**

01:59.587 --> 02:01.155
All right, red tags,
front of the line!

02:01.189 --> 02:02.523
Red tags,
front of the line.

02:02.556 --> 02:04.492
Wedding bus blew a tire
and flipped!

02:04.525 --> 02:05.759
26-year-old female.

02:05.793 --> 02:07.295
Second- and third-degree burns

02:07.328 --> 02:08.462
to her neck,
chest, and left arm.

02:08.496 --> 02:11.299
Kalu, you're up.

02:11.332 --> 02:12.933
[ Moaning ]
Trauma Six.

02:12.966 --> 02:14.902
EMT: Guy was ejected
30 feet from the vehicle.

02:14.935 --> 02:16.237
Multiple chest
contusions,

02:16.270 --> 02:17.771
acute respiratory distress
on the scene,

02:17.805 --> 02:18.839
sluggish pupillary
response.

02:18.872 --> 02:20.708
How long have you
been doing CPR?
12 minutes.

02:20.741 --> 02:21.875
Have you shocked him?
Three times.

02:21.909 --> 02:23.711
We got to crack him.
Dr. Browne, I got this.

02:23.744 --> 02:25.446
You take the next one.
All right, Bay Five.

02:25.479 --> 02:29.783
[ Indistinct chatter ]

02:29.817 --> 02:31.819
We secured the foreign object
and staunched the bleeding,

02:31.852 --> 02:33.854
but didn't want to touch it
otherwise.

02:33.887 --> 02:37.758
**

02:37.791 --> 02:39.727
Good thing.
It nicked her carotid.
What is it?

02:39.760 --> 02:41.195
Right now it's
a little Dutch boy

02:41.229 --> 02:42.330
keeping her from
bleeding out.

02:42.363 --> 02:45.233
Pulse ox is dropping.
She's at 87.

02:45.266 --> 02:46.900
O2 sats down to 83.

02:48.902 --> 02:49.970
Forget about the neck,
Claire.

02:50.003 --> 02:51.272
Treat her like
any other patient.

02:51.305 --> 02:52.673
What are the first
steps?

02:52.706 --> 02:54.475
Airway, breathing,
circulation.

02:54.508 --> 02:56.644
Good. Grab a kit.

02:56.677 --> 03:03.917
**

03:03.951 --> 03:11.359
**

03:11.392 --> 03:18.566
**

03:18.599 --> 03:21.302
I need help here!
Somebody, help!

03:21.335 --> 03:22.736
Murphy, go!

03:22.770 --> 03:26.006
[ People groaning ]

03:26.039 --> 03:27.641
Let's go.

03:27.675 --> 03:28.842
Trauma Three.

03:28.876 --> 03:32.446
**

03:32.480 --> 03:36.484
[ Woman speaks indistinctly
over P.A. ]

03:36.517 --> 03:43.824
**

03:43.857 --> 03:44.992
I can't stop the bleeding.

03:45.025 --> 03:46.594
[ Monitor beeps rapidly ]

03:48.929 --> 03:51.399
He's bleeding out.
Do something.

03:51.432 --> 03:54.034
[ Beeping continues ]

03:54.067 --> 03:57.971
**

03:58.005 --> 04:01.709
I need a urinary catheter,
14-gauge needle,

04:01.742 --> 04:03.644
arterial guide wire,
occlusion balloon,

04:03.677 --> 04:04.412
and 20 cc of saline,
stat.

04:04.445 --> 04:09.383
-- Captions by VITAC --

04:09.417 --> 04:16.390
**

04:16.424 --> 04:19.693
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

04:19.727 --> 04:28.936
**

04:28.969 --> 04:30.804
EMT #2:
What's he doing?
I have no idea.

04:30.838 --> 04:33.641
Well, you don't have one,
so I'm making a REBOA.

04:33.674 --> 04:34.975
A what?

04:37.077 --> 04:38.679
A REBOA.

04:39.847 --> 04:40.681
Is that even a word?

04:40.714 --> 04:42.916
A REBOA will occlude
the damaged artery

04:42.950 --> 04:44.084
and stop the bleeding.

04:44.117 --> 04:53.427
**

04:53.461 --> 05:02.336
**

05:02.370 --> 05:05.005
Release the pressure.

05:05.038 --> 05:09.977
[ Beeping slows ]

05:10.010 --> 05:13.481
BP is stabilizing.
90 over 60.

05:13.514 --> 05:17.685
[ Beeping continues ]

05:17.718 --> 05:19.653
Nice work, Dr. Murphy.

05:19.687 --> 05:21.355
I made a REBOA.

05:22.723 --> 05:23.724
[ Gasping ]

05:23.757 --> 05:24.825
Oxygen is dropping to 89.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.026
All right. Light.

05:26.059 --> 05:27.795
Open wide for me.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.730
Throat's swollen
from smoke inhalation.

05:29.763 --> 05:30.731
Cric kit.

05:30.764 --> 05:33.767
Do you see soot
in her mouth or nose?
No.

05:33.801 --> 05:35.703
She doesn't need a cric.
She needs an escharotomy.

05:35.736 --> 05:38.005
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

05:38.038 --> 05:43.043
**

05:43.076 --> 05:44.778
[ Gasps ]

05:44.812 --> 05:47.381
[ Beeping slows ]

05:47.415 --> 05:49.450
Sats are going back up.
92 and rising.

05:49.483 --> 05:51.084
Circumferential
neck burns.

05:51.118 --> 05:53.921
The shrinking charred skin
is acting like a noose.

05:53.954 --> 05:56.457
Escharotomy relieves
the constriction.

05:56.490 --> 05:58.091
Are you getting enough
air now, ma'am?

05:58.125 --> 05:59.960
Yes. Thank you.

05:59.993 --> 06:01.595
Now get her out of
this petri dish

06:01.629 --> 06:03.764
and into an isolation ward
in the burn unit ASAP.

06:03.797 --> 06:04.965
Yes, sir.

06:07.635 --> 06:09.470
Your heart's
a bit muffled.

06:09.503 --> 06:10.838
Am I having
a heart attack?

06:10.871 --> 06:12.673
No, but it's not
completely good news.

06:12.706 --> 06:13.907
Cardiac tamponade.

06:13.941 --> 06:15.175
He needs
a pericardiocentesis.

06:15.208 --> 06:16.877
Yes, I'm aware of that.

06:16.910 --> 06:19.913
18-gauge and 55 cc syringe,
please.

06:19.947 --> 06:21.415
We need a FAST ultrasound
in here.

06:21.449 --> 06:22.583
They're both in use.

06:22.616 --> 06:23.751
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

06:23.784 --> 06:25.753
You don't have imaging.
You could puncture his heart.

06:25.786 --> 06:28.456
Is the xiphoid in the same place
as it was 20 years ago?

06:28.489 --> 06:38.466
**

06:38.499 --> 06:39.933
**

06:39.967 --> 06:42.836
[ Beeping slows ]

06:45.706 --> 06:47.641
[ Chuckles ]

06:47.675 --> 06:49.009
A REBOA.

06:49.042 --> 06:50.544
Ballsy.

06:50.578 --> 06:51.679
Could've gone
really wrong.

06:51.712 --> 06:54.748
Yes, well, it didn't.

06:54.782 --> 06:55.749
It's a cowboy move --

06:55.783 --> 06:59.119
something you would never
even dream of trying.

06:59.152 --> 07:01.088
How many times is Shaun gonna
have to prove himself

07:01.121 --> 07:02.790
before you give him
a shot?

07:02.823 --> 07:05.225
Woman over PA:
Dr. Rolendez, O.R. 6.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.761
[ Monitor beeping slowly ]

07:07.795 --> 07:13.501
**

07:13.534 --> 07:15.035
What happened in the E.R.?

07:15.068 --> 07:17.070
Swan girl came in
and you hesitated.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.707
I wasn't hesitating.
I was thinking of a game plan.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.775
Murphy was thinking
of the game plan.

07:21.809 --> 07:23.544
You got overwhelmed.

07:23.577 --> 07:24.578
I wasn't.

07:24.612 --> 07:26.614
First trauma --
it happens.

07:26.647 --> 07:29.850
You have to think clearly,
quickly, methodically.

07:29.883 --> 07:31.785
You need to think
a little more like Shaun.

07:33.554 --> 07:36.189
A little more.
Not identically.

07:40.027 --> 07:43.497
[ Whimpering ]

07:43.531 --> 07:45.733
[ Screams ]

07:45.766 --> 07:47.868
[ Cries ]

07:50.237 --> 07:53.607
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:53.641 --> 07:55.042
How you doing?

07:55.075 --> 07:57.010
Sorry.

07:57.044 --> 07:58.812
Sorry.
That's a stupid question.

07:58.846 --> 08:02.750
[ Sobs ]

08:02.783 --> 08:04.084
You're maxed out
on morphine.

08:04.117 --> 08:08.088
I'll hold off
until it reloads.

08:08.121 --> 08:11.725
[ Shaky breathing ]

08:11.759 --> 08:13.193
How bad is it?

08:13.226 --> 08:15.629
We're making
good progress.

08:15.663 --> 08:18.666
I'll have to, uh, debride
any deroofed blisters

08:18.699 --> 08:20.000
to prevent a secondary
nosocomial and then --

08:20.033 --> 08:21.802
I need a mirror.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.103
It's the least you can do

08:23.136 --> 08:25.806
since you can't even look me
in the eye.

08:29.076 --> 08:39.052
**

08:39.086 --> 08:42.122
[ Crying ] Oh, my God.

08:42.155 --> 08:46.059
**

08:46.093 --> 08:47.661
[ Exhales deeply ]

08:47.695 --> 08:52.700
**

08:52.733 --> 08:57.037
Do you know how many hideous
$300 bridesmaid dresses

08:57.070 --> 09:00.608
I've had to buy in
the last two years?

09:00.641 --> 09:04.077
I decided that
when I got married,

09:04.111 --> 09:07.581
my bridesmaids are gonna wear
black cocktail dresses

09:07.615 --> 09:10.250
so they can use them again,
you know?

09:12.986 --> 09:14.822
[ Sobs ]

09:14.855 --> 09:17.658
But now...

09:17.691 --> 09:19.793
now I-I'm Freddy Krueger.

09:19.827 --> 09:21.695
[ Inhales sharply ]

09:21.729 --> 09:23.964
Who's gonna want
to marry this?

09:23.997 --> 09:27.835
[ Groaning ]

09:27.868 --> 09:29.102
I'm gonna find a nurse,

09:29.136 --> 09:31.839
have her adjust your, uh --
your morphine drip.

09:31.872 --> 09:35.709
[ Moaning ]

09:37.645 --> 09:38.946
Okay.

09:38.979 --> 09:39.713
You hit your face.

09:39.747 --> 09:41.715
Your jaw got stuck.
It hurts.

09:41.749 --> 09:43.350
So, this shot I just gave you
is gonna knock you out

09:43.383 --> 09:44.685
so that I can fix that.

09:44.718 --> 09:45.986
Hang tight.

09:46.019 --> 09:48.255
Crash patients
status check?
23 people total.

09:48.288 --> 09:50.223
One fatality on site,
lost one in the E.R.

09:50.257 --> 09:51.324
Examined all the red tags.

09:51.358 --> 09:53.694
Got 13 yellow and green
still in the waiting room.

09:53.727 --> 09:55.863
I'll take whoever's up next.
Marco Magallenes --

09:55.896 --> 09:57.865
severed femoral artery,
crushed femur.

09:57.898 --> 10:00.934
I did the REBOA and then
installed a temporary shunt.

10:00.968 --> 10:03.771
Here are his CT
and MRI results.

10:08.041 --> 10:10.778
Find someone else
for whoever's up next.

10:12.312 --> 10:14.014
Oh, finally.

10:16.083 --> 10:17.284
[ Jaw cracks ]

10:17.317 --> 10:23.090
**

10:23.123 --> 10:28.896
**

10:28.929 --> 10:31.999
[ Woman crying ]

10:32.032 --> 10:34.134
Excuse me.
Are you Marco's family?

10:34.167 --> 10:35.368
Ricardo: Yes.

10:35.402 --> 10:39.006
We just found out that my cousin
didn't survive the accident.

10:39.039 --> 10:42.175
I'm sorry.

10:42.209 --> 10:44.311
It's a bit much.
I'm so sorry.

10:44.344 --> 10:47.147
I'm Dr. Melendez,
and this is Dr. Murphy.

10:47.180 --> 10:48.716
I'm Ricardo.

10:48.749 --> 10:50.450
I'm M-Marco's father.

10:50.483 --> 10:54.387
This is, uh, his mother, Lorena,
and this is Sonia.

10:54.421 --> 10:56.456
They were getting
married tonight.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.058
How's my son?

10:58.091 --> 10:59.693
Marco's femur
was completely shattered,

10:59.727 --> 11:02.129
and his lower leg
isn't getting enough blood.

11:03.430 --> 11:05.298
Can you save his leg?

11:05.332 --> 11:07.868
Marco suffered
too much bone fragmentation.

11:07.901 --> 11:10.170
We can't fix it.

11:10.203 --> 11:12.740
Our only choice
is to amputate.

11:12.773 --> 11:14.341
[ Sobbing ]

11:14.374 --> 11:15.375
Mija.

11:15.408 --> 11:23.683
**

11:28.756 --> 11:30.457
Bay Five needs
a grade three hyphema.

11:30.490 --> 11:31.992
Head CT and page
ophthalmology?

11:32.025 --> 11:33.026
You read my mind.

11:33.060 --> 11:34.361
Been a while.

11:34.394 --> 11:36.163
How you holding up
pulling an all-nighter?

11:36.196 --> 11:39.266
I'll manage, but if you
can find me a caffeine IV,

11:39.299 --> 11:40.968
it'd be helpful.
Please move!

11:43.103 --> 11:45.038
Melendez: Tough night.
Jessica: Yeah.

11:45.072 --> 11:46.106
Thanks for coming.

11:46.139 --> 11:47.808
It's part of the job.

11:47.841 --> 11:50.110
So, when's the big day?

11:50.143 --> 11:52.813
Uh, we haven't
set it yet.

11:52.846 --> 11:54.181
Oh, where is
it gonna be?

11:54.214 --> 11:56.817
We'll figure it out.

11:56.850 --> 11:58.318
Maybe a beach
somewhere.

11:58.351 --> 11:59.920
We should talk
about this later.

11:59.953 --> 12:01.388
What? I like beaches.

12:01.421 --> 12:04.024
If you have a more
romantic idea...

12:04.057 --> 12:06.226
My family likes churches.

12:08.195 --> 12:09.396
We should talk
about this later.

12:09.429 --> 12:13.967
Dr. Lim, I think one of your
yellows is about to turn red.

12:14.001 --> 12:16.103
Hey.

12:16.136 --> 12:18.271
Farrar: I've got my wedding
all planned out.

12:18.305 --> 12:20.908
I've got the dress,
and I've got the flowers.

12:20.941 --> 12:22.810
All I need is a groom.

12:24.144 --> 12:26.213
You available,
Dr. Murphy?

12:26.246 --> 12:27.514
No.

12:27.547 --> 12:29.549
You don't want
some love?

12:29.582 --> 12:32.886
No. No, I don't.
I don't want love.

12:36.990 --> 12:39.459
Dr. Glassman,
neural consult, bay three.

12:39.492 --> 12:41.461
Thank you.

12:41.494 --> 12:43.831
[ Woman speaks indistinctly
over P.A. ]

12:45.498 --> 12:46.466
Hey!

12:46.499 --> 12:47.968
I was here first.

12:48.001 --> 12:49.937
Shaun.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.471
Shaun!

12:51.504 --> 12:53.206
My patient's scans
are very important.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.842
Well, my patient's
important, too.

12:54.875 --> 12:57.911
I need to see
my patient's scans.

12:57.945 --> 12:59.346
Is your patient
pre-op or post-op?

12:59.379 --> 13:02.015
Pre-op.

13:02.049 --> 13:03.316
Okay, I'll give you
the computer,

13:03.350 --> 13:04.985
but you need to
apologize first.

13:05.018 --> 13:07.020
Okay, I'm sorry.
Turn it on.

13:12.592 --> 13:15.829
Why was Marco's family
crying when Dr. Melendez

13:15.863 --> 13:19.332
told them his leg would
need to be amputated?

13:19.366 --> 13:22.502
Well, their son's leg
is about to be cut off.

13:22.535 --> 13:25.472
It's sad.
Crying is normal.

13:25.505 --> 13:28.108
But when your options
are amputation or death,

13:28.141 --> 13:29.943
amputation is good news.

13:29.977 --> 13:32.980
People need time to adjust
to big changes.

13:33.013 --> 13:35.983
Marco's family didn't even get
a chance to pray for a miracle.

13:36.016 --> 13:43.623
**

13:43.656 --> 13:47.928
Mm.
It's not possible.

13:47.961 --> 13:51.064
The bone damage
is too severe.

13:51.098 --> 13:52.933
A rod implantation
won't work.

13:52.966 --> 13:55.168
There's nothing
to anchor into,

13:55.202 --> 13:57.437
and the shunt won't
last long enough

13:57.470 --> 14:00.273
to do reconstruction.

14:00.307 --> 14:02.409
There are no
other options.

14:05.678 --> 14:08.949
What if we could replace
the entire femur?

14:12.419 --> 14:14.154
We're making him
a new femur.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.957
With a 3D printer?

14:16.990 --> 14:18.558
3D-printed bones have
only successfully

14:18.591 --> 14:21.028
been done with
the mandible.
We know.

14:21.061 --> 14:22.996
That's a fairly
small bone.
We know.

14:23.030 --> 14:25.032
A femur has to support
the weight of the entire body.

14:25.065 --> 14:27.434
This one will be titanium.
It can work.

14:27.467 --> 14:30.303
It's an interesting idea...

14:30.337 --> 14:32.072
but I need to think on it.

14:32.105 --> 14:34.541
Right now we still got seven
yellow tags waiting.

14:34.574 --> 14:36.009
What do you have
to think about?

14:36.043 --> 14:37.577
It's a good idea.
It's a brilliant idea.

14:37.610 --> 14:39.179
The kid has brilliant ideas.
That doesn't mean --

14:39.212 --> 14:41.448
No, it was my idea,
and I'm aware of the risks --

14:41.481 --> 14:43.516
infection, clotting,
hardware failure...

14:43.550 --> 14:44.584
Death.

14:44.617 --> 14:46.619
It wasn't your idea.
It was my idea!

14:46.653 --> 14:49.422
And the risks are significant,
but isn't that their call?

14:49.456 --> 14:51.424
Don't we have to --
Maybe he said something,

14:51.458 --> 14:53.060
and then you said something,
and together, you --

14:53.093 --> 14:54.928
My idea.
Completely my idea.

14:54.962 --> 14:57.697
The "brilliant" idea
is 100% my brilliant idea.

14:57.730 --> 14:59.332
Why is that a problem
for you?

14:59.366 --> 15:02.335
Maybe because I've known you
for six months.

15:02.369 --> 15:04.371
Every day we learn
new things.

15:04.404 --> 15:06.606
Today, you learned
I'm brilliant.

15:06.639 --> 15:08.141
The idea was brilliant.

15:08.175 --> 15:09.642
And it was mine.

15:09.676 --> 15:13.213
And if anyone can do this
brilliant surgery, it's you.

15:13.246 --> 15:16.049
Flattery --

15:16.083 --> 15:17.284
also brilliant.

15:17.317 --> 15:23.223
**

15:23.256 --> 15:24.657
[ Door opens ]

15:24.691 --> 15:27.194
Claire:
Sleeping on the job?

15:27.227 --> 15:29.729
[ Sighs ] Just needed some
fresh air.

15:29.762 --> 15:32.132
Feels like
I'm suffocating in there.

15:34.001 --> 15:36.336
She's in pain,
spilling her guts out,

15:36.369 --> 15:39.539
and every time I open my mouth,
I sound like an idiot.

15:39.572 --> 15:42.475
Dr. Kalu --
unable to talk to women.

15:42.509 --> 15:43.576
There's a first.

15:43.610 --> 15:46.079
If you're not gonna be helpful,
Claire, just leave.

15:48.148 --> 15:52.485
You don't need to talk.
Just listen to her.

15:52.519 --> 15:55.255
You get to come out here,
clear your head.

15:55.288 --> 15:58.491
She's trapped in there, alone
with her thoughts, her fears.

15:58.525 --> 16:01.361
You don't think
she wants to get out?

16:01.394 --> 16:04.097
You are her escape.

16:04.131 --> 16:10.703
**

16:10.737 --> 16:13.573
You want to put a fake femur
into Marco's leg?

16:13.606 --> 16:15.608
It's not fake.
It's real.

16:15.642 --> 16:18.111
It's not a real bone.
We're making it out of titanium.

16:18.145 --> 16:19.146
It's still real.

16:19.179 --> 16:20.513
That's incredible.

16:20.547 --> 16:23.116
And Marco will be able
to walk, run, climb?

16:23.150 --> 16:25.152
And swim.

16:25.185 --> 16:27.454
Hopefully.
That's the intention.

16:27.487 --> 16:30.190
Well, have you done
the surgery before?

16:30.223 --> 16:32.159
I haven't.
We'll be the first.

16:34.094 --> 16:36.029
Well, nobody has ever attempted
this surgery

16:36.063 --> 16:37.597
with a bone as large
as the femur.

16:37.630 --> 16:40.433
I believe it's a viable option,
but there are risks.

16:40.467 --> 16:43.203
Risks?
Could Marco die?

16:43.236 --> 16:45.305
In my estimation,
there's a 10% chance

16:45.338 --> 16:47.107
he won't make it.
Then no.

16:47.140 --> 16:48.441
I'm not losing my son.

16:48.475 --> 16:51.244
Wait. If there's a chance
we can save Marco's leg,

16:51.278 --> 16:53.046
we should at least
discuss this some more.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.081
That's what he'd want.

16:54.114 --> 16:55.382
He'd want to live.

16:55.415 --> 16:57.450
He'd want to
have a life.

16:57.484 --> 16:59.052
I know him.

16:59.086 --> 17:00.587
He'd want to
take the chance.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.822
I will never forgive myself
if Marco died

17:02.855 --> 17:06.593
because I made
a reckless decision.

17:06.626 --> 17:08.195
Whose decision
is this?

17:08.228 --> 17:10.063
Does he have
a healthcare proxy?

17:10.097 --> 17:11.464
I don't know
what that is.

17:11.498 --> 17:13.333
When the accident
happened,

17:13.366 --> 17:15.335
were you on the way to your
wedding or on the way back?

17:15.368 --> 17:17.537
We were headed
to the wedding.

17:17.570 --> 17:20.073
Marco's parents are
the next of kin.

17:20.107 --> 17:21.174
They decide.

17:21.208 --> 17:27.447
**

17:27.480 --> 17:29.549
Please...

17:29.582 --> 17:31.418
amputate our son's leg.

17:31.451 --> 17:32.585
[ Sobs ]

17:36.223 --> 17:37.324
Murphy.

17:39.859 --> 17:41.161
[ Sighs ]

17:44.264 --> 17:45.565
Why is the primary
closure on the stump

17:45.598 --> 17:50.237
so vital in amputation
surgery?
For a proper
prosthetic fitting.

17:50.270 --> 17:52.139
Why are you
marrying Jessica?

17:53.740 --> 17:55.775
Why does anyone
get married?

17:55.808 --> 17:57.544
I don't know.

17:59.212 --> 18:01.348
I love her.

18:01.381 --> 18:03.716
I don't understand why
having someone to love

18:03.750 --> 18:05.752
is so important
to everyone.

18:07.354 --> 18:09.289
You have to
stand down.

18:09.322 --> 18:11.391
You can't amputate
Marco's leg.
Why not?

18:11.424 --> 18:14.561
I filed an emergency injunction
to stop the surgery.

18:18.298 --> 18:19.766
You were in
a car accident.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.701
Your neck
was punctured.

18:21.734 --> 18:23.436
The repair surgery
went well.

18:23.470 --> 18:24.771
You're gonna have to
stay put for a week

18:24.804 --> 18:27.407
before we can
release you.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.509
You're very lucky
to be alive.

18:33.446 --> 18:35.148
[ Coughs ]

18:37.184 --> 18:41.788
[ Raspily ] My wife,
Jenna Hensel -- is she okay?

18:41.821 --> 18:43.756
Can I see her?

18:47.860 --> 18:49.929
She's not listed.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.431
That's a good thing.

18:51.464 --> 18:53.500
She's probably still
in the waiting room.

18:53.533 --> 18:55.335
I'll find her
and bring her up.

18:55.368 --> 18:57.404
She'll be relieved
to know you're okay.

18:57.437 --> 19:00.207
Okay.

19:00.240 --> 19:01.574
What the hell am I
supposed to do with

19:01.608 --> 19:02.675
an unconscious patient

19:02.709 --> 19:04.211
whose leg is a ticking
time bomb?

19:04.244 --> 19:05.312
Judge Singh is en route.

19:05.345 --> 19:06.713
She wants to hear
from both parties

19:06.746 --> 19:08.181
and the doctors
on the case.

19:08.215 --> 19:09.816
I have to testify?

19:09.849 --> 19:10.917
Hopefully not.
Hopefully not.

19:10.950 --> 19:12.685
I thought you
would be happy.

19:12.719 --> 19:14.354
You thought you
could save the leg,

19:14.387 --> 19:16.256
and I didn't want that not
happening because the parents

19:16.289 --> 19:17.357
are afraid to make
a tough call.

19:17.390 --> 19:18.858
It's their call
to make.

19:18.891 --> 19:20.727
And if the accident
happened an hour later,

19:20.760 --> 19:22.195
it would be the wife's.

19:22.229 --> 19:23.730
And she wants
the fake leg.

19:23.763 --> 19:25.598
It's not fake.

19:25.632 --> 19:26.699
I thought
you didn't believe

19:26.733 --> 19:28.768
in just blindly following
protocol.

19:28.801 --> 19:29.936
He's their son.

19:29.969 --> 19:31.671
Nobody's gonna love
him more than them.

19:31.704 --> 19:32.672
Seriously?

19:32.705 --> 19:34.607
All parents love
all children

19:34.641 --> 19:35.742
more than anybody else?

19:35.775 --> 19:37.877
People get divorced
all the time.

19:37.910 --> 19:39.446
How often do they
give up their kids?

19:39.479 --> 19:40.747
So, if this was us,

19:40.780 --> 19:42.549
you'd want your parents
to decide over me?

19:42.582 --> 19:44.451
I didn't say that.
You kind of did.

19:45.785 --> 19:48.455
I was saying,
there needs to be rules,

19:48.488 --> 19:50.657
that there needs to be
bright red lines telling us

19:50.690 --> 19:52.525
who gets to make
these calls.

19:52.559 --> 19:54.227
It's the parents' call.

19:54.261 --> 19:55.695
Not anymore.

19:55.728 --> 19:57.664
Now it's the judge's.

19:57.697 --> 19:59.832
How much time does Marco have
left on the temporary shunt?

19:59.866 --> 20:01.901
Three hours,

20:01.934 --> 20:03.670
and then his leg
will die.

20:06.739 --> 20:08.341
Okay.
Mm.

20:08.375 --> 20:10.843
**

20:16.949 --> 20:19.752
Dr. Torture returns.

20:19.786 --> 20:22.021
Thought I'd scared you off
for good.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.923
Pick a movie.

20:23.956 --> 20:26.793
You deserve to get out of this
room for a little while, too.

20:29.061 --> 20:32.532
You think "Groundhog Day"
is gonna make a difference?

20:32.565 --> 20:36.469
"I'm torturing you, but, hey,
you get to watch a funny movie."

20:36.503 --> 20:38.705
That is sort of what
I was going for, yeah.

20:42.975 --> 20:44.344
I'm sorry.

20:46.879 --> 20:49.749
I wish there was something else
I could do.

20:49.782 --> 20:50.983
How do you know
there isn't?

20:51.017 --> 20:52.752
This is protocol.
This is what they teach us.

20:52.785 --> 20:54.487
I lucked out.

20:54.521 --> 20:57.957
I got the world's greatest
expert on burn victims?

20:57.990 --> 21:00.427
You know everything
that can be done.

21:03.863 --> 21:07.434
He loves to rock-climb,
scuba dive, bungee-jump.

21:07.467 --> 21:08.968
This is insane.

21:09.001 --> 21:12.505
His leg is literally dying
while we sit here reminiscing.

21:12.539 --> 21:15.575
Please. We're trying to figure
out what your son would want.

21:15.608 --> 21:17.377
He would want
to live.
I want that, too,

21:17.410 --> 21:20.780
but if there's a way that
we can save Marco's leg,

21:20.813 --> 21:22.014
he'd want me to do it.

21:22.048 --> 21:26.486
Mija, Do you know what
he wanted most of all?

21:29.021 --> 21:30.857
He wanted to marry you.

21:30.890 --> 21:34.026
He wanted to spend his life with
you, have children with you.

21:34.060 --> 21:36.095
Now, he can do all that.

21:36.128 --> 21:39.832
He can be happy
with a prosthetic leg.

21:41.401 --> 21:43.870
He's young,
and he's strong.

21:43.903 --> 21:46.406
Mija, he can get
through this.

21:46.439 --> 21:51.611
**

21:51.644 --> 21:54.947
When we met --
I don't care about
your stories.

21:54.981 --> 21:58.885
I don't care that
you met rock-climbing

21:58.918 --> 22:00.720
or kayaking or whatever.

22:00.753 --> 22:03.790
I just want --
We met in rehab.

22:03.823 --> 22:10.697
**

22:10.730 --> 22:13.633
[ Man speaks indistinctly
over P.A. ]

22:13.666 --> 22:15.768
Hey, are either of you
Jenna Hensel?

22:15.802 --> 22:17.370
I haven't seen Jenna

22:17.404 --> 22:19.472
since we took pictures
at the hotel.

22:19.506 --> 22:20.873
But she got on the bus?

22:20.907 --> 22:22.975
Yeah, she was sitting
with Noomi.

22:23.009 --> 22:29.148
**

22:29.181 --> 22:31.017
I think she's still
out there.

22:31.050 --> 22:33.019
Hey, guys!
We've got to go back.
Where?

22:33.052 --> 22:34.954
To the crash site.
Now.

22:34.987 --> 22:37.757
He never wanted
you to know.

22:40.092 --> 22:41.794
He's an addict.

22:41.828 --> 22:45.064
He replaced one addiction for
another one -- a healthier one.

22:45.097 --> 22:48.535
But he needs --
What?

22:48.568 --> 22:52.071
He needs to wakeboard or
he'll drink himself to death?

22:52.104 --> 22:53.072
This is ridiculous.

22:53.105 --> 22:54.541
No, it's not!

22:54.574 --> 22:56.175
We talked about it
a lot.

22:56.208 --> 22:58.645
It's pretty much
all you do in rehab.

22:58.678 --> 23:01.948
Marco has clarity for
the first time in his life.

23:01.981 --> 23:03.716
He knows what
makes him happy.

23:03.750 --> 23:06.185
He knows his weaknesses.

23:06.218 --> 23:09.656
He's not as strong
as you think.

23:09.689 --> 23:12.425
And that's okay, but --

23:12.459 --> 23:13.960
Marco cheated on you.

23:16.996 --> 23:18.965
It was about
a month ago.

23:18.998 --> 23:22.502
He was overwhelmed with
the wedding and the planning.

23:22.535 --> 23:24.571
He ran into
an ex-girlfriend.

23:24.604 --> 23:26.673
It only happened once.

23:28.140 --> 23:30.643
You're lying.

23:30.677 --> 23:33.713
You're upset that he
had secrets from you, so --

23:33.746 --> 23:35.615
No, she's not lying.

23:38.718 --> 23:40.887
Mija, he -- he was --
he was so upset.

23:40.920 --> 23:41.888
He does love you.

23:41.921 --> 23:44.156
Okay, maybe we're digressing
here a little bit.

23:44.190 --> 23:45.858
And we really don't
have the time.

23:45.892 --> 23:48.761
It matters.

23:48.795 --> 23:52.198
She doesn't
know him like --

23:52.231 --> 23:54.200
maybe none of
us do, but...

23:54.233 --> 23:59.472
but we are his parents,
and you're not his wife.

23:59.506 --> 24:00.807
Yet.

24:06.579 --> 24:08.615
[ Siren wails ]

24:08.648 --> 24:16.756
**

24:16.789 --> 24:18.257
Okay. Get the cops.
Check everywhere --

24:18.290 --> 24:20.126
other side of the road,
bushes, trees.

24:20.159 --> 24:21.994
If she was ejected from the bus,
she could be 40, 50 feet

24:22.028 --> 24:23.830
in any direction.

24:27.967 --> 24:29.235
Claire: Jenna!

24:31.671 --> 24:33.272
I found her!
I need some help!

24:33.305 --> 24:40.980
**

24:41.013 --> 24:42.014
Okay,
she's got a brain bleed.

24:42.048 --> 24:44.050
We need to get her
out of here now!

24:47.820 --> 24:49.255
Dr. Andrews.

24:49.288 --> 24:50.657
I think Celez
may be eligible

24:50.690 --> 24:52.659
for an experimental
bone treatment.

24:52.692 --> 24:53.526
Sell it to me.

24:53.560 --> 24:55.061
Well, I've been
doing some digging.

24:55.094 --> 24:57.196
San Diego Community Hospital's
burn unit

24:57.229 --> 24:59.265
has been following
a Brazilian hospital's protocol

24:59.298 --> 25:01.033
to wrap burns
in tilapia skins.

25:01.067 --> 25:03.803
Now -- Now, I know fish skins
sound a bit crazy,

25:03.836 --> 25:06.706
but -- but I was thinking we
could do the same thing here.

25:06.739 --> 25:09.809
Dr. Kalu,
I applaud your thinking.

25:09.842 --> 25:12.679
But we --
Tilapia skins contain
more collagen proteins --

25:12.712 --> 25:14.647
both types 1 and 3 --
than even human skin,

25:14.681 --> 25:17.083
which aids in tissue repair,
negating the need for grafts.
Dr. Kalu.

25:17.116 --> 25:18.851
It's shown to accelerate
healing, would reduce...
Dr. Kalu.

25:18.885 --> 25:20.086
...the risk of infection
and cut down on

25:20.119 --> 25:21.921
the patient's
physical pain.

25:21.954 --> 25:25.057
Are you finished, or would
you like to cut me off again?

25:25.091 --> 25:27.560
Okay, let's follow this
through, shall we?

25:27.594 --> 25:28.861
You have to come up
with a proposal

25:28.895 --> 25:29.896
for the experimental
treatment,

25:29.929 --> 25:32.331
get it approved by our
institutional review board,

25:32.364 --> 25:35.234
get your hands
on medical-grade tilapia skins,

25:35.267 --> 25:38.070
and then we --
Well, I thought you could help
expedite the process.

25:38.104 --> 25:40.306
[ Scoffs ]

25:40.339 --> 25:43.142
You think I could bring it down
from three months to two hours?

25:44.911 --> 25:47.246
You finish
the debridement?

25:47.279 --> 25:49.048
Okay, I'll take over
from here.

25:49.081 --> 25:50.850
Okay.
Hey.

25:50.883 --> 25:52.852
Keep thinking
outside the box.

25:52.885 --> 25:54.687
Initiative is good.

25:58.057 --> 25:59.759
[ Police radio chatter ]

25:59.792 --> 26:04.230
**

26:04.263 --> 26:05.998
I'm in. Bag her.

26:06.032 --> 26:06.933
Did you get me
the drill?

26:06.966 --> 26:08.701
The fire truck had one.
What's going on?

26:08.735 --> 26:09.736
Her pupil's blown.

26:09.769 --> 26:10.903
She has a subdural
hematoma,

26:10.937 --> 26:12.639
causing increased
intracranial pressure.

26:12.672 --> 26:13.973
If I don't
alleviate it now,

26:14.006 --> 26:15.875
there's no way she makes it
to the hospital alive.

26:15.908 --> 26:17.309
[ Drill whirrs ]

26:17.343 --> 26:19.078
[ Sighs ] Okay.

26:19.111 --> 26:28.788
**

26:28.821 --> 26:31.290
[ Drill whirrs ]

26:31.323 --> 26:38.164
**

26:38.197 --> 26:39.331
[ Chuckles ]

26:40.967 --> 26:42.902
Unconscious female.
Flail chest.

26:42.935 --> 26:44.637
I had to do a burr hole
in field.

26:44.671 --> 26:46.405
Her sats are in
the low 70s.

26:50.276 --> 26:51.744
[ Jenna gasping ]

26:55.081 --> 26:57.083
She's good to go
to the O.R.

26:58.450 --> 27:00.119
Subdural hematoma?

27:00.152 --> 27:02.188
She had decerebrate posturing,
a blown left pupil.

27:02.221 --> 27:03.923
When I passed the drill bit
through her skull,

27:03.956 --> 27:05.324
a whole lot of blood
pooled out.

27:05.357 --> 27:06.859
Good call.

27:08.260 --> 27:09.829
[ Door opens ]

27:11.363 --> 27:14.266
Uh, San Diego Community Hospital
called.

27:14.300 --> 27:15.868
They're sending
the tilapia skins.

27:15.902 --> 27:17.369
They're medevacing
them in.

27:17.403 --> 27:19.672
Should be here
within the hour.

27:19.706 --> 27:21.741
Celez...

27:21.774 --> 27:24.210
you meet the criteria
for an experimental treatment

27:24.243 --> 27:25.211
that I think will
prevent you

27:25.244 --> 27:27.246
from having to undergo
skin grafts.

27:27.279 --> 27:29.281
Hold up.
How did this even happen?

27:29.315 --> 27:31.283
Well, I found out
San Diego's trial

27:31.317 --> 27:33.319
allows for multi-site
collaborations.

27:33.352 --> 27:35.688
So, there's no need for us
to get our own I.R.B.

27:35.722 --> 27:38.791
They give us the skins,
we provide the patient data.

27:38.825 --> 27:40.359
Fish skins?
[ Chuckles ]

27:40.392 --> 27:42.895
The tilapia skins have been
cleaned and sterilized.

27:42.929 --> 27:45.131
They're perfectly safe.

27:48.434 --> 27:49.869
You'll do it?

27:52.972 --> 27:54.406
I'll do it.

27:56.508 --> 27:58.845
Andrews:
Well done, Dr. Kalu.

27:58.878 --> 28:00.379
Well done.

28:00.412 --> 28:02.181
...so help you God?

28:02.214 --> 28:04.350
Yes.

28:04.383 --> 28:07.720
Dr. Melendez
can tell you --
He has.

28:07.754 --> 28:10.222
But the fake femur is yours,
though, right?

28:10.256 --> 28:12.859
How confident are you
in its design?
It's not fake!

28:12.892 --> 28:15.194
Shaun, she needs
to know --
I know what
she needs to know.

28:15.227 --> 28:17.396
She needs to know
will it work.

28:17.429 --> 28:20.299
She needs to know
how long it will last.

28:22.168 --> 28:23.169
Yes.

28:23.202 --> 28:24.737
Okay.

28:30.943 --> 28:31.878
He's his doctor?

28:31.911 --> 28:34.213
He is a surgical resident.
He's very gifted.

28:34.246 --> 28:36.115
Is he going to answer
my questions?

28:36.148 --> 28:39.285
Shaun, I really need you
to focus.

28:39.318 --> 28:42.488
**

28:42.521 --> 28:45.124
Marco is running
out of time!
Just let him answer!

28:45.157 --> 28:47.226
No, we already know the answer.
They don't know.

28:47.259 --> 28:48.795
This thing has never
been done before.

28:48.828 --> 28:50.262
Be quiet!

28:50.296 --> 28:57.770
**

28:57.804 --> 29:00.539
His toes are changing color.

29:00.572 --> 29:07.980
**

29:08.014 --> 29:10.983
He's clotting. That's bad.
Page Dr. Melendez stat!

29:15.121 --> 29:16.022
Murphy, what do we got?
The shunt is clotting.

29:16.055 --> 29:19.191
It's restricting blood flow.
It is failing.

29:19.225 --> 29:20.259
All right, we need
a decision now.

29:20.292 --> 29:22.128
Are we cutting off the leg
or replacing the bone?

29:22.161 --> 29:23.996
There's no doubt in my mind
that Marco's parents

29:24.030 --> 29:26.866
and fiancée all love Marco,
but it's become clear --

29:26.899 --> 29:28.400
Now.
I need a decision now.

29:30.837 --> 29:32.805
His parents know him
as their child.

29:32.839 --> 29:35.041
Sonia knows him
as a man.

29:35.074 --> 29:37.543
Replace the femur.
[ Gasps ]

29:37.576 --> 29:40.046
Let's go!

29:40.079 --> 29:42.815
Thank you!
Thank you.

29:42.849 --> 29:50.857
**

29:50.890 --> 29:53.425
And there's the bleed.
See it?
Yes, sir.

29:53.459 --> 29:56.562
You ever clip
an intracranial artery before?

29:56.595 --> 29:58.430
No, sir.

29:58.464 --> 29:59.866
Go for it.

29:59.899 --> 30:07.406
**

30:07.439 --> 30:09.942
Just like every
first time --

30:09.976 --> 30:14.080
you're a little excited,
a little nauseous.

30:14.113 --> 30:16.815
Hopefully nobody
gets hurt.

30:19.651 --> 30:27.159
**

30:27.193 --> 30:34.466
**

30:34.500 --> 30:36.502
Is it good to go?

30:36.535 --> 30:38.037
It's very good.

30:38.070 --> 30:39.005
Forceps.

30:39.038 --> 30:42.141
**

30:42.174 --> 30:44.310
[ Inhales sharply ]

30:44.343 --> 30:46.312
You ready?

30:46.345 --> 30:47.613
Yes.

30:47.646 --> 30:55.487
**

30:55.521 --> 31:03.362
**

31:03.395 --> 31:11.303
**

31:11.337 --> 31:19.178
**

31:19.211 --> 31:22.014
Be careful the clip blades
don't catch

31:22.048 --> 31:24.917
any perforated arteries.

31:24.951 --> 31:26.685
I don't seen any vessels
in the way.

31:26.718 --> 31:28.420
Then what are you
waiting for?

31:28.454 --> 31:33.659
**

31:33.692 --> 31:35.027
Very nice.

31:35.061 --> 31:36.128
Thank you.

31:40.299 --> 31:41.400
Everything's dry.

31:41.433 --> 31:43.369
Say goodbye
and close the roof.

31:46.372 --> 31:47.473
We need to get blood
back into his leg

31:47.506 --> 31:49.408
in the next minute or so,

31:49.441 --> 31:51.543
or I'm gonna have
to amputate after all.

31:51.577 --> 31:54.213
Insulin's hanging,
loaded him with calcium.

31:54.246 --> 31:55.414
Best I can do.

31:55.447 --> 31:56.949
Let's release
the clamps.

31:59.385 --> 32:01.320
Check for capillary
refill.

32:02.621 --> 32:08.360
**

32:08.394 --> 32:14.100
**

32:14.133 --> 32:16.735
Blood flow is restored.

32:16.768 --> 32:19.138
EKG is normal.

32:21.340 --> 32:23.609
Okay. Kim, I want to
hear words like

32:23.642 --> 32:26.012
"variability" and "Delta".

32:26.045 --> 32:27.479
Give them to me.

32:29.315 --> 32:32.318
I'm waiting patiently.

32:32.351 --> 32:35.154
I'm not getting
anything.

32:35.187 --> 32:36.555
Show me.

32:36.588 --> 32:39.391
**

32:44.163 --> 32:45.497
Claire:
Check the leads.

32:45.531 --> 32:52.538
**

32:52.571 --> 32:54.373
Still nothing.

32:54.406 --> 32:56.342
Maybe there will be
some neuroplasticity.

32:56.375 --> 33:00.579
Her brain --
i-it could rewire itself.

33:00.612 --> 33:02.248
No.

33:03.782 --> 33:05.684
Zero brain activity.

33:05.717 --> 33:07.286
I don't know why,
but she's gone.

33:07.319 --> 33:12.658
**

33:13.825 --> 33:25.337
**

33:25.371 --> 33:27.473
[ Sighs ]
What?

33:27.506 --> 33:29.408
Your neurosurgery patient
that died tonight --

33:29.441 --> 33:30.776
there's something
you should know.

33:30.809 --> 33:32.344
What?

33:32.378 --> 33:40.252
**

33:40.286 --> 33:43.689
Melendez: Now, Marco, I want you
to try and move your toes.

33:43.722 --> 33:51.130
**

33:51.163 --> 33:54.166
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:54.200 --> 33:55.467
I can't.

33:55.501 --> 33:56.202
Is he okay?

33:56.235 --> 33:57.303
We're not sure
if the bone --

33:57.336 --> 33:58.570
He's not gonna die?

33:58.604 --> 34:00.139
H-He's not gonna
get an infection?

34:00.172 --> 34:02.508
His body's not
gonna reject --
No, no. We're monitoring
him very closely.

34:02.541 --> 34:04.543
The biggest threat
is behind --
He moved.

34:05.377 --> 34:06.745
He moved.

34:06.778 --> 34:13.519
**

34:13.552 --> 34:16.155
It worked.

34:16.188 --> 34:17.656
You'll have a long
recovery ahead --

34:17.689 --> 34:19.625
months of physical therapy.

34:19.658 --> 34:21.260
But for now, all you
have to do is rest.

34:21.293 --> 34:22.828
Thank you.

34:22.861 --> 34:27.633
Thank you for saving my life --
for saving my leg.

34:27.666 --> 34:30.068
Thank you.
You're welcome, sir.

34:34.440 --> 34:36.708
Are you ready to finish
what we started?

34:38.610 --> 34:41.380
Get well first.

34:41.413 --> 34:43.415
There's plenty of time
for a wedding.

34:43.449 --> 34:51.723
**

34:51.757 --> 34:53.725
Thank you.
You're welcome, sir.

34:53.759 --> 34:55.127
Thank you.

34:55.161 --> 35:02.501
**

35:02.534 --> 35:03.702
You look good.

35:03.735 --> 35:06.572
Tough.
Like Aquaman.

35:06.605 --> 35:08.907
[ Laughs ]

35:08.940 --> 35:12.311
Mm.
I look like sushi.

35:12.344 --> 35:14.213
Everybody loves sushi.

35:14.246 --> 35:15.581
[ Both laugh ]

35:15.614 --> 35:16.682
It's only for
six months.

35:16.715 --> 35:19.318
Your new skin should have
completely grown in by then.

35:19.351 --> 35:21.920
Should have
minor scarring.

35:21.953 --> 35:23.489
Thank you.

35:25.691 --> 35:27.593
I misjudged you.

35:29.361 --> 35:31.397
You judged me
just right.

35:31.430 --> 35:38.670
**

35:38.704 --> 35:40.372
[ Knock on door ]

35:43.442 --> 35:45.744
Is she still sleeping?

35:45.777 --> 35:46.845
You haven't
told her yet?

35:46.878 --> 35:49.348
No.

35:49.381 --> 35:51.817
Can I have a moment
please?

35:51.850 --> 35:53.452
Of course.

35:53.485 --> 36:00.259
**

36:00.292 --> 36:03.262
How soon after you found
Jenna at the crash site

36:03.295 --> 36:04.863
did you intubate her?

36:04.896 --> 36:06.732
Almost immediately.

36:06.765 --> 36:08.600
I did a sternal rub.

36:08.634 --> 36:10.302
Uh, she had decerebrate
posturing.

36:10.336 --> 36:11.903
Her left pupil
was blown.

36:11.937 --> 36:13.639
I knew she had
a subdural hematoma,

36:13.672 --> 36:16.542
so I intubated,
did the burr hole.

36:16.575 --> 36:19.378
She also had
a flail chest.

36:19.411 --> 36:21.747
Did you check her breathing
after you intubated her?

36:21.780 --> 36:22.914
Yes.

36:25.417 --> 36:27.819
Well, at least
I-I think I did.

36:29.955 --> 36:34.226
Dr. Lim told me that when
Jenna came into the E.R.,

36:34.260 --> 36:35.927
she wasn't ventilating
properly.

36:35.961 --> 36:38.297
You inserted the tube
too deep

36:38.330 --> 36:40.866
into her right
main stem bronchus

36:40.899 --> 36:42.934
of her injured lung.

36:42.968 --> 36:45.271
We had no way of knowing

36:45.304 --> 36:49.275
how long she was hypoxic
before we gave her the EEG.

36:49.308 --> 36:59.285
**

36:59.318 --> 37:03.622
I drilled a perfect
burr hole into her skull

37:03.655 --> 37:05.291
on the side of the road
in the middle of the night,

37:05.324 --> 37:08.694
and I-I-I screw up
her intubation?

37:08.727 --> 37:12.831
Yes. It was tough conditions
for anyone -- resident or not.

37:12.864 --> 37:15.534
Any one of us could have
made the same mistake.

37:23.074 --> 37:30.282
**

37:30.316 --> 37:32.984
I had a woman come
into the E.R. once...

37:33.018 --> 37:34.520
[ Clears throat ]

37:34.553 --> 37:37.756
...a mother,
51 years old.

37:37.789 --> 37:40.459
Francine Parker.

37:40.492 --> 37:42.661
She had two boys.

37:42.694 --> 37:44.896
She had a cough --

37:44.930 --> 37:49.000
a bad one --
but a cough.

37:49.034 --> 37:51.870
I checked her out, gave her some
antibiotics, sent her home.

37:51.903 --> 37:55.741
Six hours later,
she was rolled into the E.R.

37:55.774 --> 37:59.745
She had had a heart attack,
and I missed it, and...

37:59.778 --> 38:01.513
she died.

38:04.049 --> 38:09.688
Not one day...goes by
when I don't think about her.

38:11.757 --> 38:14.960
She was your first.

38:14.993 --> 38:17.563
My fourth, actually.

38:19.865 --> 38:22.868
You're not gonna
forget this.

38:22.901 --> 38:25.371
You never forget.

38:25.404 --> 38:27.873
But I don't know, maybe
we're better off for it

38:27.906 --> 38:30.876
the next time around.

38:30.909 --> 38:33.311
You got to find a way
to keep going.

38:36.582 --> 38:38.717
Yeah.

38:38.750 --> 38:41.520
Go home.
Get some rest.

38:41.553 --> 38:42.888
I haven't even
told her yet.

38:42.921 --> 38:44.356
You're not going to.

38:45.724 --> 38:48.427
You made a mistake.
You're too close to this.

38:48.460 --> 38:50.562
I'm not gonna allow you
to talk to the family

38:50.596 --> 38:54.600
or anyone else outside
this hospital about this.

38:56.101 --> 38:58.970
Do we understand
each other?

38:59.004 --> 39:00.672
Yes, sir.

39:00.706 --> 39:06.011
**

39:06.044 --> 39:10.682
* I don't have
all the words to say *

39:12.584 --> 39:16.755
* I'm still healing
from my mistakes *

39:18.924 --> 39:23.128
* I'll take the weight
if it makes you stronger *

39:25.531 --> 39:30.402
* I don't want to leave you
in this place *

39:34.606 --> 39:36.708
I called San Diego Community
Hospital and thanked them

39:36.742 --> 39:37.876
for including us
in their study.

39:37.909 --> 39:40.512
They said they were
happy to do it.

39:40.546 --> 39:44.015
And they asked that I pass along
their thanks to you

39:44.049 --> 39:47.953
for your very generous donation
to their burn unit.

39:52.624 --> 39:54.059
I know you come from
a wealthy family.

39:54.092 --> 39:56.595
I don't begrudge that,
but you...

39:56.628 --> 40:01.467
can't open your wallet
every time a patient's in need.

40:01.500 --> 40:04.703
The lines can get real blurry
real fast.

40:07.172 --> 40:09.140
Yes, sir.

40:09.174 --> 40:11.577
[ Elevator bell dings ]

40:11.610 --> 40:21.487
**

40:21.520 --> 40:31.196
**

40:31.229 --> 40:36.067
* Who am I to try
and save you? *

40:37.836 --> 40:39.805
* I ain't gonna hide

40:39.838 --> 40:41.507
* You have to fight today

40:41.540 --> 40:43.074
What's this?

40:43.108 --> 40:45.076
My healthcare proxy.

40:45.110 --> 40:46.912
Jess, nothing's
gonna happen.

40:46.945 --> 40:50.048
Really?
That's good to know.

40:50.081 --> 40:51.683
* I won't let you down

40:51.717 --> 40:52.951
* I won't let you down

40:52.984 --> 40:56.522
* No, no, no

40:56.555 --> 40:58.223
* But I won't let you down

40:58.256 --> 40:59.691
* I won't let you down

40:59.725 --> 41:01.727
* No, no, no

41:01.760 --> 41:10.936
**

41:10.969 --> 41:14.205
Well, that was quite a night.
[ Chuckles ]

41:14.239 --> 41:16.107
Been a doctor
for a long while --

41:16.141 --> 41:20.211
don't remember a night
quite like that one.

41:20.245 --> 41:23.549
Why did Nurse Farrar ask
if I wanted love?

41:23.582 --> 41:25.584
'Cause she's a nosy...

41:28.587 --> 41:31.089
Shaun, you really
don't want love?

41:31.122 --> 41:34.693
I loved Steve
and my rabbit.

41:34.726 --> 41:36.562
Not anymore.

41:36.595 --> 41:38.964
You don't love them
anymore?

41:38.997 --> 41:41.833
No, I don't.
They're dead.

41:41.867 --> 41:45.737
You can't love someone
if they're dead.

41:45.771 --> 41:49.074
Well, I've lost
people I love.

41:49.107 --> 41:52.043
I miss them, and it hurts,
but I still love them.

41:52.077 --> 41:58.083
**

41:58.116 --> 42:00.018
I don't want love.

42:04.623 --> 42:05.891
Okay.

42:09.661 --> 42:13.131
You want breakfast?

42:13.164 --> 42:15.967
Can I have four pancakes
instead of three?

42:16.001 --> 42:17.335
You can have five.

42:17.368 --> 42:19.605
I only want four.

42:19.638 --> 42:21.773
Okay.

42:21.807 --> 42:24.175
Okay.

42:24.209 --> 42:27.679
**

42:32.984 --> 42:41.226
**

42:41.259 --> 42:49.367
**

42:49.400 --> 42:57.676
**

42:57.709 --> 43:05.851
**
